INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (143,1,'2021-03-02 02:18:46','2021-03-02 02:18:46','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>How to surf Like a Pro</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":142,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://frostsnowboards.local/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/snown3-1024x732.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The place has a rich history of craftsmanship. Local snowboarders, surfboards, and skiers started developing the noble art of snow surfing in the early 1980s.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The movement spread to Europe and North America and gained broader visibility in the 2000s. It still involves a lot of experimentation, but the equipment required is highly efficient already.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Snow surfers ride a board shaped explicitly for the mountains that combines aspects of the surfboard, snowboard, skateboard, and even sandboard. Some athletes even use wax to increase grip.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unlike traditional snowboards, surf snowboards are not meant to be ridden using bindings. As a result, it is harder to keep a balance, more difficult to maneuver, and it is considerably slower than snowboarding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Post 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','129-revision-v1','','','2021-03-02 02:18:46','2021-03-02 02:18:46','',129,'http://frostsnowboards.local/129-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
