INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (162,1,'2021-03-02 03:55:01','2021-03-02 03:55:01','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":164,\"width\":578,\"height\":333,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://frostsnowboards.local/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/post4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-164\" width=\"578\" height=\"333\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When riding champion-turned-canine coach Chris de Aboitiz recorded himself with his canines getting some surf off the shoreline of Sydney, Australia, this week, the video went viral. Furthermore, with the manner in which de Aboitiz\'s canines are hopping over his shoulders while he rides in waves, it\'s not difficult to perceive any reason why. It\'s a sweet stunt, however how might you show your canine to hop on the board with you in any case?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Everything returns to getting conduct,\" says de Aboitiz. His work as a canine coach in his local america is pull in conduct discipline for canines. Instructing your canine to surf is \"an interesting method to have a good time, yet to truly associate with your canine, and its conduct,\" he says. Here are five steps to get your canine out in the water, and on the load up, in the blink of an eye.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Surf With Your Dog','','publish','open','open','','surfing-measure-to-look','','','2021-03-02 04:08:13','2021-03-02 04:08:13','',0,'http://frostsnowboards.local/?p=162',0,'post','',0);
